<p>
    I stayed in BVM for 6 years and made many friends there. While I was in BVM, I developed
    an interest in soccer and played for my school team in inter-school tournaments. Also, I participated in
    debates and theater events. Then in 10th grade, I moved to Delhi Public School in Noida from where I completed my
    high school. After that I took admission in Amity University in Noida. I took Computer Science as my major 
    because I always loved video games and wanted to learn more about how they are developed. But pretty soon I
    realised that Computer Science was much more than just making games or applications.  
</p>
